Trailer: Bachelorette - a bachelorette bombshell Suitors scurry for a game plan when it's revealed two of them will be going home in this episode airing Thursday 1st October.
PT0M29S http://www.smh.com.au/action/externalEmbeddedPlayer?id=d-43pfi 620 349 October 1, 2015 Autoplay On Off Video feedback Video settings Michael Turnbull is actually a real estate agent After a protracted preamble, Sam shared her first cocktail party kiss for the series with Sasha Mielczarek.
"It was exactly how it was supposed to feel," Frost said about the passionate moment.
"It was exactly how it was supposed to feel".
For his part Sasha was left lost for words.
Advertisement "Well, to be honest, I wanted to do that on the tango date. Tonight was the right time and place. That was it. It was good. A bit lost for words, actually."
Frost previously pecked Dave Billsborrow during his cricket ground date.
Sam Frost tangoes with Sasha Mielczarek
Earlier in the episode the 30 year old construction manager impressed Sam with his willingness to learn the tango and remove his shirt.
Sasha, reportedly the son of a rebel bikie gang member, also opened up about his early life and being raised by his step father.
"He's been my number-one supporter, he took me under his wing like I was his only child," Sasha said.
Real estate agent and soccer player Michael Turnbull poses topless.
Less fortunate was owl bearing sleep technician Drew Woolford from Queensland who did not receive a rose at the end of the episode.
Frost also took Richie, Michael, Dave, Tony, Will, Kieran, Kane and Davey on a group date that involved shirt removal.
The men were required to pose topless with dogs for an animal charity fundraiser.
"And you know what people say? Seeing a man with his dog is what he's going to be like with a child," she said to host Osher Gunsberg.
Michael Turnbull, who was recently revealed to not having the professional soccer credentials he initially claimed , most impressed Sam during the photoshoot.
Comic relief came from Mandurah man Kane Bulk who rapped for Sam about his decision to come on the show. He said:
"Yo, yo, yo, check it /
Way back at the start of the year/ Through the hard times and tear after tear/
I saw an ad for The Bachelorette Season 1/
So I jumped online and filled the forms - it had begun yeah!/
Now, here I am, which I never though way back when/
But look at me now, sitting in front of a perfect ten/
I'm very thankful for the roses and more group dates/
I have more to offer, so I'll grab the wine and you grab the plates/
I'll give you the hot tip/
When I first saw you, you made me bite my bottom lip?
Happiness is on the top, I must say/
Treating people with respect, everyone equal/
That's my life, namaste."
The Bachelorette airs again on Thursday October 1st at 7:30pm on Channel Ten
